renderState

public final void renderState()
DataRows are susceptible to attaining schemas containing TheoreticalValues. The SchemaSafeDataStructure class can correct for this and identify the true schema if the data exists in columns, but the individual schemas may persist. This method will apply the true schema to each DataRow to eliminate TheoreticalValues from them and clean up the overall schema integrity of the table. It is recommended that after large adds, removals, transformations, etc, this method be called to create a constant schema throughout, however, this was designed as a non-essential method because the presence of TheoreticalValues in the individual DataRow schemas is not an issue in the table determining the proper schema.
